        "title": "refactor(sqlite): canonicalize memory and proxy storage",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- canonicalize built-in memory tables and FTS/vector index names under the per-agent database schema\n- migrate shipped generic-name memory rows into canonical tables transactionally, fail closed on conflicts, and rebuild derived FTS/vector tables\n- move debug-proxy captures into shared state and migrate shipped sidecar sessions, duplicate-preserving events, and gzip blobs from default or active legacy override paths\n- archive migrated proxy sources while preserving CA certificates; leave sources intact on malformed data or conflicts\n- align database-first docs and raw-SQLite ownership guardrails\n\nSessions and transcript migration/storage are intentionally out of scope.\n\n## Validation\n\n- clean Testbox `pnpm check:changed --base c2297e4924e5506854ea7bc1b61bbeac32595ba1`\n- clean Testbox `pnpm build`\n- 287-test focused Testbox matrix across memory, proxy, doctor migrations, shared state, CLI, providers, and QA Lab\n- targeted reruns: 74 doctor migration tests, 35 doctor E2E tests, and 54 memory index tests\n- `pnpm lint:kysely`\n- `pnpm db:kysely:check`\n- `pnpm check:database-first-legacy-stores`\n- `oxfmt --check` on all touched files\n\n## Stack\n\nStacked on `refactor/sqlite-remaining-alignment-20260616` for isolated review.",
